{"id":"234163986_Present_Position_and_Potential_Developments_Some_Personal_Views_Statistical_Theory_The_Prequential_Approach","abstract":"The prequential approach is founded on the premises that the purpose of statistical inference is to make sequential probability forecasts for future observations, rather than to express information about parameters. Many traditional parametric concepts, such as consistency and efficiency, prove to have natural counterparts in this formulation, which sheds new light on these and suggests fruitful extensions.","authors":["Alexander Philip Dawid"],"meta":["January 1984Journal of the Royal Statistical Society Series A (General) 147(2):278-292","DOI:10.2307/2981683"],"references":["243785101_A_Model_Fitting_Analysis_of_Daily_Rainfall_Data","242423103_Adaptive_software_reliability_modeling","236586057_Graphical_and_Recursive_Models_for_Contingency_Tables","230663850_Partial_Likelihood","38385239_The_Conditional_Probability_Integral_Transformation_and_Applications_to_Obtain_Composite_Chi-Square_Goodness-of-Fit_Tests","4895246_Exogeneit","285443873_An_Asymptotic_Equivalence_of_Choice_of_Model_by_Cross-Validation_and_Akaike's_Criterion","275690674_Statistical_Inference_for_Stochastic_Processes","271196714_New_Look_at_Statistical-Model_Identification","269855587_Statistical_Inference_for_Markov_Processes","268012205_On_a_Concept_of_Partial_Sufficiency_L-Sufficiency","266223252_Martingales_Recent_Developments_Results_and_Applications","266095863_Probabilistic_Weather_Forecasting_with_Spatial_Dependence","265993376_Some_Logical_Aspects_of_the_Fiducial_Argument","257925521_An_asymptotic_equivalence_of_choice_of_model_by_cross-validation_and_Akaike's_Criterion","251210696_Remarks_on_Efficiency_in_Estimation_for_Branching_Processes","247670406_Sufficiency_Prediction_and_Extreme_Models","245580756_Bartlett_adjustments_to_the_likelihood_ratio_statistic_and_the_distribution_of_the_maximum_likelihoo","245524216_Asymptotic_normality_for_sums_of_depen